    "created_at": "2014-11-14T12:03:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-11-14T12:03:41Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@takluyver So, there is a nice function already in IPython that can install into the system and replace existing, but there needs to be an interface to that. Issues: \n- should the code that calls install_kernel_spec be in a kernl's setup.py?\n- it needs a flag for a system install\n- it needs a flag for \"update\" (pip's usage) (eg, replace == True in kernelspec.py)\n\nSo, we just need to add `--system` and `--update` options to all setup.py, and allow pip to pass those in (`--update` is already an option to pip... does setup.py see that?)\n"
  },
